# CODEOWNERS — required human review on high-risk paths
#
# Source decision: docs/specs/2026-05-26-commit-pr-pipeline-gates.md (D4).
# Rationale: automated LLM review is advisory (nondeterministic => never a required
# gate); blanket human review would bottleneck autonomous flows and can deadlock a
# solo author. So required human review is routed to high-consequence paths ONLY;
# everything else is gated by deterministic CI.
#
# Two owners are listed so the non-author can always approve (no solo-author deadlock).
#
# NOTE: this file only *requests* code-owner review. Making that review *required*
# on these paths is a branch-protection setting (GitHub repo admin). WI-538 enabled
# and proved it (2026-06-11), then it was deliberately SUSPENDED until MentoMate is
# in production (operator ruling) — re-arming is WI-617, a pre-launch checklist item.
# Until then, these lines are advisory only.

# Payments / subscription — mischarge / revenue risk
**/billing/**                    @jojorgen @crowka

# Authentication — security / privilege-escalation risk
**/auth/**                       @jojorgen @crowka
**/clerk*                        @jojorgen @crowka

# Database migrations + schema — irreversible data-loss risk
packages/database/drizzle/**     @jojorgen @crowka
packages/database/src/schema/**  @jojorgen @crowka

# CI/CD pipeline — self-protecting; secret-exfiltration risk
.github/workflows/**             @jojorgen @crowka
